%matplotlib inline
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D
from matplotlib import cm
from matplotlib.ticker import LinearLocator, FormatStrFormatter
from math import cos


Tm = 1
Xm = 1


def solution(N, M):
    net = np.zeros((N, M))
    h = Xm / (M - 1)
    dt = Tm / (N - 1)
    
    for m in range(M):
        net[0][m] = cos(m*h)
    for n in range(N):
        net[n][M-1] = cos(Tm + 2*n*dt)
        
    for n in range(N-1):
        for m in range(M-1):
            net[n+1][m] = net[n][m] + 2*dt/h * (net[n][m+1] - net[n][m])

    return net


def print3d(net, N, M, title='title'):
    T = np.linspace(0, Tm, N)
    X = np.linspace(0, Xm, M)
    X, T = np.meshgrid(X, T)
    fig = plt.figure()
    ax = fig.gca(projection='3d')
    surf = ax.plot_surface(T, X, net, cmap=cm.coolwarm,
                       linewidth=0, antialiased=True)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel('t')
    plt.ylabel('X')
    plt.show()
    return

#N, M = (int(i) for i in input().split())
print3d(solution(100, 100), 100, 100, 'Bad net (1)')
print3d(solution(200, 90), 200, 90, 'Good net (2)')
print3d(solution(100, 45), 100, 45, 'Good net (3)')

N_ = 500
T_, dt = np.linspace(0, Tm, N_, retstep = True)
X_, h = np.linspace(0, Xm, N_, retstep = True)
X_, T_ = np.meshgrid(X_, T_)
net_ = np.zeros((N_, N_))
for n in range(N_):
    for m in range(N_):
        net_[n][m] = cos(m*h + 2*n*dt)

fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.gca(projection='3d')
surf = ax.plot_surface(T_, X_, net_, cmap=cm.coolwarm,
                   linewidth=0, antialiased=True)
plt.title('U(x, t) = cos(x+2t)')
plt.xlabel('t')
plt.ylabel('X')
plt.show()
